Albondigas (meatballs in almond sauce)
  --Cook's Illustrated

Picada
1/4 c slivered almonds
1 slice hearty white sandwich bread, torn into 1" pieces
2 tbsp evoo
3 tbsp minced fresh parsley
2 garlic cloves, minced

Process almonds in food processor until finely ground, ~20 s. Add bread and process until bread is finely ground, ~15 s. Transfer mixture to 12" nonstick skillet. Add oil and cook over medium heat, stirring often, until mixture is golden brown, 3-5 min. Transfer to bowl. Stir in parsley and garlic and set aside. Wipe skillet clean with paper towels.

Meatballs
1 slice hearty white sandwich bread, torn into 1" pieces
1 large egg
2 tbsp water
2 tbsp chopped fresh parsley
2 garlic cloves, minced
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp pepper
1 lb ground pork
1 tbsp evoo
1/2 c finely chopped onion
1/2 tsp paprika
1 c chicken broth
1/2 c dry white wine
1/4 tsp saffron threads, crumbled
1 tsp sherry vinegar

Process bread in foor processor until finely ground, ~15 s. Add egg, water, 1 tbsp parsley, garlic, salt, and pepper and process until smooth paste forms, ~20 s, scraping down sides of bowl as necessary. Add pork and pulse until combined, ~5 pulses. Remove processor blade. Moisten hands and form generous 1 tbsp of mixture into 1" round meatballs and transfer to plate; repeat with remaining pork mixture to form ~24 meatballs. Heat oil in skillet over medium heat until shimmering. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, 4-6 min. Add paprika and cook until fragrant, ~30 s. Add broth and wine and bring to simmer. Stir in saffron. Add meatballs and adjust heat to maintain simmer. Cover and cook until meatballs register 160F, 6-8 min, flipping meatballs once. Stir in picada and continue to cook, uncovered, until sauce has thickened slightly, 1-2 min longer. Off heat, stir in vinegar. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Transfer to platter, sprinkle with remaining parsley and serve.
